<treatmentCitation id="0AF68F06FFC0FF89D4B5F9A3DD84F9E6" author="Eigenmann, C" box="[1005,1240,1556,1575]" page="394" pageId="1" pageNumber="516" year="1910">
<bibRefCitation id="EFC6D4E6FFC0FF89D4B5F9A3DD84F9E6" author="Eigenmann, C" box="[1005,1240,1556,1575]" pageId="1" pageNumber="516" pagination="375 - 511" refId="ref21689" refString="Eigenmann, C. H. 1910. Catalogue of the freshwater fishes of tropical and south temperate America. In: Reports of the Princeton University expeditions to Patagonia 1896 - 1899. Zoology: 375 - 511." type="book chapter" year="1910">Eigenmann 1910: 394</bibRefCitation>
</treatmentCitation>
]. Gender masculine. Originally proposed as a subgenus of 
<taxonomicName id="4C57D294FFC0FF89D387F983DC08F986" authorityName="Bleeker" authorityYear="1858" box="[1247,1364,1588,1607]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Doradidae" genus="Hemidoras" kingdom="Animalia" order="Siluriformes" pageId="1" pageNumber="516" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B9237505FFC0FF89D387F983DC08F986" box="[1247,1364,1588,1607]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="516">Hemidoras</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</treatmentCitationGroup>
</paragraph>
